289
00:21:40,955 --> 00:21:42,605
Like they have powers or something.

290
00:21:42,690 --> 00:21:44,550
Karen, these are patients.

291
00:21:44,625 --> 00:21:46,485
They have been through trauma.

292
00:21:49,497 --> 00:21:53,527
And perhaps now they are
capable of something we're not.

293
00:21:55,202 --> 00:21:58,432
We have brain scans now.

294
00:21:58,506 --> 00:22:03,036
DID patients have changed their
body chemistry with their thoughts.

295
00:22:06,481 --> 00:22:08,801
He's just trying to scare us.

296
00:22:08,883 --> 00:22:11,193
He was having a full
conversation with himself.

297
00:22:13,654 --> 00:22:16,884
What was that line about?
"The food is waiting."

298
00:22:16,957 --> 00:22:20,977
Does everyone get how wacked this is
and that we need to get out of here now?

299
00:22:29,770 --> 00:22:31,790
No.

300
00:22:31,872 --> 00:22:34,432
Please, keep your area neat.

301
00:22:34,509 --> 00:22:36,129
The bathroom, it's unacceptable.

302
00:22:36,210 --> 00:22:38,670
To make it easy, I've color-coded these.

303
00:22:38,746 --> 00:22:43,976
Use the blue bottle for the floor and
the pink bottle for the ceramic surfaces.

304
00:22:48,556 --> 00:22:49,916
Uh...

305
00:23:08,208 --> 00:23:13,698
Patricia has reminded me that
I was sent to get you for a reason.

306
00:23:13,781 --> 00:23:16,581
That you are sacred food.

307
00:23:18,285 --> 00:23:20,715
And I promise not to bother you again.

308
00:23:34,101 --> 00:23:36,691
Maybe he has a dog or something.

309
00:23:36,771 --> 00:23:38,941
You think he's gonna feed us to his dogs?

310
00:24:13,073 --> 00:24:14,073
Casey.

311
00:24:16,043 --> 00:24:17,043
Casey!

312
00:24:35,763 --> 00:24:37,223
My name's Hedwig.

313
00:24:37,297 --> 00:24:39,067
I have red socks.

314
00:24:45,773 --> 00:24:47,813
He's on the move.

315
00:24:50,778 --> 00:24:51,778
What?

316
00:24:55,716 --> 00:24:58,106
He's... on...

317
00:24:58,185 --> 00:24:59,605
the...

318
00:24:59,687 --> 00:25:01,117
move.

319
00:25:03,423 --> 00:25:04,693
Who?

320
00:25:05,660 --> 00:25:07,650
Someone's coming for you

321
00:25:07,728 --> 00:25:10,618
and you're not gonna like it.

322
00:25:10,698 --> 00:25:12,688
You guys make noises in your sleep.

323
00:25:12,767 --> 00:25:13,767
Tell us.

324
00:25:14,835 --> 00:25:16,765
I'm not supposed to say.

325
00:25:18,072 --> 00:25:22,762
But he's done awful things to people
and he'll do awful things to you.

326
00:25:22,843 --> 00:25:24,263
I have blue socks, too.

327
00:25:24,344 --> 00:25:25,884
We're his food?

328
00:25:30,150 --> 00:25:32,050
How old are you?

329
00:25:32,787 --> 00:25:33,947
Nine.

330
00:25:36,390 --> 00:25:40,130
So you're not the guy that took us?

331
00:25:40,828 --> 00:25:42,158
No.

332
00:25:44,331 --> 00:25:45,951
You're not the lady?

333
00:25:46,033 --> 00:25:48,293
What are you, blind?

334
00:25:48,368 --> 00:25:51,228
You don't know how they think?

335
00:25:51,305 --> 00:25:53,785
No, they don't tell me much.

336
00:25:53,874 --> 00:25:55,314
I just ate a hot dog.

337
00:25:56,911 --> 00:26:00,051
Could you help us, Hedwig?

338
00:26:01,782 --> 00:26:04,842
No, I'm not even supposed to be here.

339
00:26:04,919 --> 00:26:07,909
I stole the light from Mr. Dennis,
but he'll be back real soon.

340
00:26:07,988 --> 00:26:12,078
I can't steal the light for too
long or he'll know and get angry.

341
00:26:12,159 --> 00:26:13,329
Etcetera.

342
00:26:15,996 --> 00:26:17,076
See you!

343
00:26:17,164 --> 00:26:18,274
Wait.

344
00:26:22,002 --> 00:26:23,772
We heard something.

345
00:26:25,906 --> 00:26:28,336
We didn't understand it,

346
00:26:29,910 --> 00:26:31,350
but now we do.

347
00:26:34,181 --> 00:26:36,701
Do you know what we heard?

348
00:26:36,784 --> 00:26:38,394
What did you hear?

349
00:26:39,820 --> 00:26:41,120
Come here.

350
00:26:43,390 --> 00:26:45,130
I'll whisper it to you.

351
00:26:47,394 --> 00:26:48,404
Okay.

352
00:27:01,108 --> 00:27:02,238
This guy...

353
00:27:05,946 --> 00:27:07,916
is coming for you.

354
00:27:12,987 --> 00:27:14,407
You're a big fibber.

355
00:27:14,488 --> 00:27:16,088
I never lie, Hedwig.

356
00:27:17,257 --> 00:27:19,807
But Mr. Dennis,

357
00:27:19,894 --> 00:27:22,884
he said that he followed
those two girls for four days

358
00:27:22,963 --> 00:27:25,093
and that he knew

359
00:27:25,165 --> 00:27:27,765
that they were the ones that he would want.

360
00:27:30,537 --> 00:27:32,787
When you're not around,

361
00:27:32,873 --> 00:27:35,103
Dennis and the lady talk about it.

362
00:27:35,175 --> 00:27:38,065
They talk about how he wants a boy this time.

363
00:27:38,145 --> 00:27:39,495
They're going to give him you.

364
00:27:39,579 --> 00:27:42,399
No, Miss Patricia, she said...

365
00:27:42,482 --> 00:27:44,502
She said she's not mad at me anymore.

366
00:27:44,584 --> 00:27:46,774
She sings to me sometimes.

367
00:27:46,854 --> 00:27:49,764
I think Miss Patricia is
still a little mad at you.

368
00:27:50,825 --> 00:27:53,175
Miss Patricia thinks I'm...

369
00:27:53,260 --> 00:27:54,830
She thinks I'm stupid.

370
00:27:56,263 --> 00:27:58,273
She thinks I make silly mistakes.

371
00:27:59,133 --> 00:28:00,233
Look at me.

372
00:28:01,135 --> 00:28:03,335
We're like your babysitters.

373
00:28:05,239 --> 00:28:08,179
We'll let you watch TV
and make you a fun dinner.

374
00:28:10,344 --> 00:28:13,134
We all need to get out of here.

375
00:28:13,213 --> 00:28:15,543
You could show us the way out.

376
00:28:15,615 --> 00:28:18,135
We could be gone before anybody gets back,

377
00:28:18,218 --> 00:28:20,268
but we have to hurry, Hedwig.

378
00:28:20,354 --> 00:28:22,824
We have to hurry and get out of here.

379
00:28:26,226 --> 00:28:27,456
Wait a minute.

380
00:28:29,096 --> 00:28:31,116
It took forever to get this place safe

381
00:28:31,198 --> 00:28:33,088
without the nosey bodies
that work here finding out.

382
00:28:33,167 --> 00:28:35,017
You can't get out of here!

383
00:28:35,102 --> 00:28:36,192
I have to blow my nose.

384
00:28:36,270 --> 00:28:37,440
No, wait! Please don't go!

385
00:28:40,174 --> 00:28:41,144
Who's coming?

386
00:28:42,509 --> 00:28:44,299
This is seriously scary.

387
00:28:44,378 --> 00:28:45,508
No one's coming.

388
00:28:50,184 --> 00:28:51,824
He said something.

389
00:28:54,021 --> 00:28:57,521
He said something about making the room safe.

390
00:28:58,592 --> 00:29:00,192
This is all new drywall.

391
00:29:02,062 --> 00:29:03,332
What was unsafe?

392
00:29:38,298 --> 00:29:39,328
Wait.

393
00:29:40,434 --> 00:29:42,074
Wait, are we sure about this?

394
00:30:03,390 --> 00:30:06,390
Casey, you were right.

395
00:30:07,261 --> 00:30:08,981
There's something here.

396
00:30:09,063 --> 00:30:11,053
He was covering up a way out.

397
00:30:11,131 --> 00:30:12,531
Tell me if you see him.

398
00:30:16,470 --> 00:30:18,240
Casey, tell us what you see.

399
00:30:25,545 --> 00:30:27,425
He's here.

400
00:30:27,514 --> 00:30:29,204
You can't let him in! You can't let him in!

401
00:30:29,283 --> 00:30:30,423
This is our one chance.

402
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:34,210
We're not gonna make it.

403
00:30:34,288 --> 00:30:35,458
Yes, we are!

404
00:30:44,131 --> 00:30:45,131
What?

405
00:30:46,166 --> 00:30:47,426
Hey, what are you guys doing?

406
00:30:51,571 --> 00:30:52,571
Hey.

407
00:30:54,074 --> 00:30:55,584
Okay, quit it.

408
00:30:56,210 --> 00:30:57,440
Okay, guys?

409
00:30:58,112 --> 00:30:59,232
Let me in.

410
00:30:59,313 --> 00:31:02,343
Give us a second. We're changing.

411
00:31:02,416 --> 00:31:03,616
What are you guys doing?

412
00:31:05,652 --> 00:31:06,622
Let me in.

413
00:31:09,389 --> 00:31:10,989
Guys, you're not being funny.

414
00:31:22,102 --> 00:31:24,292
You're being bitches!
Now, I'm gonna slap you!

415
00:31:24,371 --> 00:31:25,431
I'm gonna slap you in your face.

416
00:31:25,505 --> 00:31:27,265
Just give me as much time as you can.

417
00:31:28,775 --> 00:31:31,025
You're gonna get me into trouble.

418
00:31:34,681 --> 00:31:35,971
Guys...

419
00:31:37,784 --> 00:31:39,254
All right, push up.

420
00:32:45,485 --> 00:32:46,485
Hey!

421
00:32:51,458 --> 00:32:52,628
Hey!

422
00:32:58,865 --> 00:33:00,465
Hey!

423
00:33:26,226 --> 00:33:28,526
I thought I lost you.

424
00:33:31,598 --> 00:33:32,868
Would you, uh...

425
00:33:34,301 --> 00:33:36,101
Would you step outside, please?

426
00:33:43,443 --> 00:33:45,533
You like to make fun of us.

427
00:33:45,612 --> 00:33:48,202
But we're more powerful than you think.

428
00:33:48,282 --> 00:33:49,782
Step outside.

429
00:33:52,552 --> 00:33:53,552
Please.

430
00:34:02,429 --> 00:34:04,529
You shouldn't trick children.

431
00:34:05,465 --> 00:34:07,525
That shows who you are.

432
00:34:13,740 --> 00:34:15,660
Look at your sweater. It's ruined.

433
00:34:15,742 --> 00:34:17,242
It's dirty.

434
00:34:19,479 --> 00:34:20,709
Remove it.

435
00:34:52,412 --> 00:34:53,712
I'm trying to be good.

436
00:35:10,630 --> 00:35:12,420
You will not see your friend again.

437
00:35:14,534 --> 00:35:16,604
She will be kept separate.

438
00:35:19,706 --> 00:35:22,296
You take off your skirt.
You take off your shirt.

439
00:35:22,376 --> 00:35:24,336
Clothes you got all dirty from the dust.

440
00:35:47,967 --> 00:35:53,757
One identity in an individual with
Dissociative Identity Disorder

441
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:54,990
can have high cholesterol.

442
00:35:55,074 --> 00:35:56,434
One.

443
00:35:56,510 --> 00:36:00,430
There have been cases where one
identity is allergic to bee stings.

444
00:36:00,514 --> 00:36:02,204
The others are not.

445
00:36:02,282 --> 00:36:06,942
Are there moments where two identities
can coexist at the same time?

446
00:36:07,020 --> 00:36:09,740
There are times when two identities

447
00:36:09,823 --> 00:36:13,313
can take the "light" or "the spot"

448
00:36:13,393 --> 00:36:15,923
or consciousness at the same time.

449
00:36:15,995 --> 00:36:18,885
This happened with a student
that I was working with.

450
00:36:18,965 --> 00:36:22,985
And her left and right hand were taking notes

451
00:36:23,069 --> 00:36:27,989
in different hand-writings about
separate things at the same time.

452
00:36:28,074 --> 00:36:31,804
The differences in the
identities can be dramatic.

453
00:36:31,878 --> 00:36:35,638
As much as the difference between you and me

454
00:36:35,715 --> 00:36:38,615
and every person in that auditorium.

455
00:36:39,819 --> 00:36:41,739
The identities have different IQ's.

456
00:36:41,821 --> 00:36:43,781
They have different physical strengths.

457
00:36:43,857 --> 00:36:47,007
One personality is a Russian weightlifter

458
00:36:47,093 --> 00:36:50,923
and can lift three times his body weight.

459
00:36:50,997 --> 00:36:53,817
Their ability to hyper-focus

460
00:36:53,900 --> 00:36:57,000
and have different experiences is astounding.

461
00:36:59,906 --> 00:37:04,356
Have these individuals,
through their suffering,

462
00:37:04,444 --> 00:37:07,384
unlocked the potential of the brain?

463
00:37:08,915 --> 00:37:12,415
Is this the ultimate doorway

464
00:37:13,720 --> 00:37:16,990
to all things we call unknown?

465
00:37:19,559 --> 00:37:23,859
Is this where our sense of
the supernatural comes from?

466
00:37:37,611 --> 00:37:39,581
It's about depth

467
00:37:41,581 --> 00:37:43,471
and curves...

468
00:37:43,550 --> 00:37:44,970
Hey, you see that one?

469
00:37:45,051 --> 00:37:46,891
It's kind of like a chenille sweater-dress.

470
00:37:51,124 --> 00:37:52,534
Who are you?

471
00:37:57,531 --> 00:37:58,731
Barry.

472
00:38:00,734 --> 00:38:01,904
I don't think you are.

473
00:38:03,803 --> 00:38:06,533
I've developed a nose for sensing

474
00:38:06,606 --> 00:38:08,606
whom I'm talking to and whom I'm not.

475
00:38:09,943 --> 00:38:11,773
Have I done something?

476
00:38:11,845 --> 00:38:14,595
You've emailed for an unscheduled appointment

477
00:38:14,681 --> 00:38:16,741
two days in a row.

478
00:38:16,816 --> 00:38:18,646
We're just feeling overwhelmed.

479
00:38:19,453 --> 00:38:20,893
Garden-variety issues.

480
00:38:22,121 --> 00:38:27,081
I think Orwell or Jade or Samuel or Heinrich

481
00:38:27,160 --> 00:38:29,920
had the light for a moment and emailed me.

482
00:38:29,996 --> 00:38:32,486
And you're here to tell me everything's okay.

483
00:38:32,566 --> 00:38:34,096
I emailed you.

484
00:38:36,703 --> 00:38:38,773
May I talk to one of them, please?

485
00:38:43,477 --> 00:38:45,127
That can't happen.

486
00:38:45,211 --> 00:38:46,701
I...

487
00:38:46,780 --> 00:38:50,480
I told them that I wanted to spend
the session with you today.

488
00:38:51,918 --> 00:38:54,808
I'm gonna ask again.

489
00:38:54,888 --> 00:38:58,648
To whom am I speaking with now?

490
00:38:58,725 --> 00:39:01,455
Dr. Fletcher, it's Barry.

491
00:39:02,195 --> 00:39:04,875
It doesn't seem like Barry.

492
00:39:04,964 --> 00:39:07,154
Barry is an extroverted leader.

493
00:39:07,233 --> 00:39:08,603
Yes, I am.

494
00:39:10,870 --> 00:39:13,430
I'm gonna take a professional guess

495
00:39:13,507 --> 00:39:17,157
based on the description of all 23 identities

496
00:39:17,243 --> 00:39:19,703
that live in Kevin's body,

497
00:39:19,779 --> 00:39:21,849
that I've gotten from Barry.

498
00:39:24,117 --> 00:39:27,787
I think I'm talking to Dennis.

499
00:39:31,124 --> 00:39:32,914
But he's been banned from the light

500
00:39:32,992 --> 00:39:35,582
because, among other reasons,

501
00:39:35,662 --> 00:39:39,992
he has a proclivity to watch
young girls dance naked,

502
00:39:40,066 --> 00:39:41,916
which he himself knows is wrong

503
00:39:42,001 --> 00:39:44,761
and has fought against with little success.

504
00:39:44,838 --> 00:39:47,588
I'm encouraged we can finally meet.

505
00:39:47,674 --> 00:39:49,104
And I've guessed this

506
00:39:49,175 --> 00:39:52,865
because you've adjusted the chocolate
dish twice since you came in here

507
00:39:52,946 --> 00:39:54,526
and I understand you have OCD.

508
00:39:55,982 --> 00:39:58,472
I see. Now, I see. That's clever.

509
00:39:58,552 --> 00:40:00,612
That's clever, but I'm not Dennis.

510
00:40:00,687 --> 00:40:03,707
And you and Patricia have
been banned from the light

511
00:40:03,790 --> 00:40:05,650
for quite a while now.

512
00:40:05,725 --> 00:40:07,975
Primarily, shall we say,
because of your beliefs.

513
00:40:08,061 --> 00:40:10,521
Patricia and Dennis are very unstable.

514
00:40:10,597 --> 00:40:11,847
I'm not Dennis.

515
00:40:11,931 --> 00:40:14,091
Have you both taken charge now?

516
00:40:14,167 --> 00:40:16,737
Please believe me, I'm Barry.

517
00:40:23,710 --> 00:40:25,200
You must forgive me.

518
00:40:25,278 --> 00:40:28,538
My job is to challenge you.

519
00:40:28,615 --> 00:40:30,835
And, as you must know by now,

520
00:40:30,917 --> 00:40:34,587
I have plenty of opinions about
how everyone should live their lives.

521
00:40:36,856 --> 00:40:38,776
Ask me something about fashion.

522
00:40:38,858 --> 00:40:40,128
I'll prove it.

523
00:40:40,860 --> 00:40:42,720
Look, look, look. Lindt.

524
00:40:45,264 --> 00:40:46,234
Yeah, look.

525
00:40:48,267 --> 00:40:50,197
You see? I'm not Dennis.

526
00:40:51,838 --> 00:40:53,658
You want me to do something else?

527
00:40:53,740 --> 00:40:55,060
You got ice cream?

528
00:40:55,141 --> 00:40:59,571
Oh, this shirt's a cotton blend anyway
and the collar is from three seasons ago.

529
00:40:59,646 --> 00:41:01,576
Snood? I mean, come on.

530
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:23,060
Jai, what health-conscious
fast food purveyor

531
00:41:23,136 --> 00:41:25,286
did you originally solicit
to buy these chicken wings

532
00:41:25,371 --> 00:41:28,731
you've so lovingly reheated
in a minor suicidal gesture?

533
00:41:28,808 --> 00:41:30,758
Hooters. And you can't just
throw them out, Dr. Fletcher.

534
00:41:30,844 --> 00:41:32,904
Oh, this is wrong on so many levels.

535
00:41:32,979 --> 00:41:37,239
